title: For Sale:  Century Arms CETME Model 58 C308 Sporter $650
postcontent: Century Arms CETME Model 58 C308 Sporter $650I have a Century Arms CETME Model 58 C308 sporter package for sale today. This package includes the rifle equipped with a picatinny top optics rail. I am including a UTG rail handguard system. 12x aluminum 20rnd German HKG3. 2x steel 20rnd German HKG3 magazines. And a rubberized dual-magazine belt pouch.For those unfamiliar, the CETME is the Spanish armaments manufacturer Centro de Estudios Tecnicos de Materiales Especiales. What has come to be known in America as the CETME (pronounced set-mee) rifle is actually a Century Arms import of demilled CETME Model 58 rifles that are reassembled into what CAI has dubbed the C308 Sporter. The CETME 58 was the foundation of what would later become the German Heckler & Koch G3 battle rifle. This CAI C308 retains all the features and benefits that the Model 58 boasts such as the awesome Spanish heavy-duty steel. The rifle is as ergonomic as you would expect any G3 pattern rifle to be and shoots extremely smoothly. The muzzle device provides a great deal of compensation and felt recoil is amazingly low for the full-power 7.62x51/308 cartridge.
